subSubSection.paragraph:
The calling song has a dominant frequency of 8.9–9.6 kHz and a high amplitude plateau between approximately 6.8 and 11.1 kHz (
Fig. 17D
). Males were found to be responsive to simulated female wing-flick responses when these were timed precisely to occur at the end of each echeme (LWP, pers. obs., 
7 January 2016
).

Measurements
(in mm; 
5 males
). Body length: 24.2–26.3 (25.4). Fore wing length: 29.5–30.4 (30.0). Fore wing width: 9.8–10.4 (10.1). Head width: 6.7–7.1 (7.0). Pronotum width: 7.0–7.6 (7.4). Abdomen width: male 6.6–7.9 (7.6).
